s  Events Giving  Office of Advancement at Chicago Office of Advancement at Peoria Office of Advancement at Rockford Office of Advancement at Urbana University of Illinois Foundation  Search for:    Masters and Doctorate Programs Home / Education / Masters and Doctorate Programs  Masters and Doctorate Programs tlowery1 2019-08-01T15:14:49-05:00 Masters and Doctorate Programs In addition to our MD Program, the University of Illinois College of Medicine has several additional highly reputable advanced degree programs in the medical sciences. Please review our programs to get a better understanding of the focus we have on advanced medical education as well as our focus on furthering the initiative of adding Diversity to these programs: Graduate Education in Biomedical Sciences (Chicago Campus) Masters of Science Degree in Medical Biotechnology (Rockford Campus) Master of Health Professions Education Master of Science in Patient Safety Leadership (Online) Graduate Diversity Programs (Chicago Campus) Medical Scientist Training Program (Chicago Campus) In addition to the Masters and Doctorate programs listed above, the College of Medicine also sponsors several joint degree masters and doctorate programs. Please click here and click on “Joint Degree Programs” for more detail on these programs. Education MD Admissions Requirements and Timeline Application Process Tuition and Financial Aid Campus Selection Curricular Programs Interview Day Student Life FAQs Contact MD Curriculum and Academics Physician Competency Reference Curricular Programs Assessment and Evaluation Scholarly and Research Opportunities Visiting Student Information DME Resources MD Student Services and Support Student Affairs Student Experience Blueprint Specialty Webinars Specialty Resource Directory MSPE MSPE Quartile in Class Calculation (2021 Graduates and forward) MSPE Quartile in Class Calculation (2019 and 2020 Graduates) Registrar Student Financial Aid and Debt Management Student Honors and Awards M